 the instructions. Eye health tips for older people How to keep your eyes healthy after the age of 60 with NHS eye tests, prescription lenses and lifestyle changes. Living with low vision Nearly 2 million people in the UK are affected by low vision. With the right help, eyesight can be maximised. Watering eyes What causes this irritating problem and how your GP may be able to help. Laser eye surgery Surgical techniques have been developed to correct eyesight and reduce the need for glasses. Sunscreen and sun safety Protect your skin against sun damage (including sunbeds) and reduce your risk of skin cancer. Caring for a black eye How to help a black eye to heal at home, and when to go to the doctor. All other articles on Eye health Videos: childhood squint Video: corneal transplant Video: eye examinations for adults Getting started Find your nearest optician Eye care for people with disabilities Find out about NHS eye care services Tools Are you at risk of diabetes? Take this short test to find out more Screening and tests Check which ones apply to you Also on NHS Choices Astigmatism Black eye Cataracts Dry eye syndrome Eyelid problems Macular degeneration Retinoblastoma ServiceSearch Find and compare services Services Diabetic eye screening Eye - accident and emergency services Ophthalmology Opticians Location Looking for other services? View services A-Z Stye Find out about styes (hordeolums) \u2013 small, painful spots that can appear on your eyelid Stop smoking Help with quitting, including what your GP can do, local services and nicotine replacement therapies 5 A DAY Whether you're cooking for a family or eating on the run, our tips and recipes can help you get your 5 A DAY NHS Choices information Choices e-newsletters Your pages Site policies Terms and conditions Editorial policy Comments policy Syndication Privacy policy Cookies policy Links policy Accessibility Sitemap Other NHS sites Summary Care Records NHS Scotland NHS Northern Ireland NHS Wales NHS Jobs 