iet and exercise tips to help your child build strong, healthy bones for life. Keep your bones strong over 65 It's never too late to look after your bone health \u2013 just follow these practical tips. Exercises for strong bones Best exercises for building and maintaining strong bones for all age groups. Food for strong bones What you eat today will help to keep your skeleton strong for the future. Are you at risk of falling? Take this simple test to work out if your risk of falling is considered \u2018low\u2019, \u2018medium\u2019 or \u2018high\u2019. Are you at risk of breaking a bone? Work out if you\u2019re at risk of osteoporosis and breaking a bone in the next 10 years. Menopause and your bone health How to keep your bones strong and healthy following the menopause. Calcium All about calcium, including good sources, how much you need and the risks of taking too much. Vitamin D All about vitamin D, including good sources, how much you need and the risks of taking too much. Strength exercises Strength exercises that can be done at home to help improve your health and mobility. Flexibility exercises Flexibility exercises for older people that can be done at home to help improve mobility and prevent falls. Balance exercises Simple balance exercises that can be done at home to help improve your health and mobility. Sitting exercises Gentle sitting exercises that can be done at home to help improve mobility and prevent falls. Are you at risk of a fall? The timed get up and go test Please enable JavaScript in order to view the video. Watch this video to find out how to test whether you or a loved one are at risk of a fall. Media last reviewed: 29\/09\/2015 Next review due: 29\/09\/2017 NHS Choices information Choices e-newsletters Your pages Site policies Terms and conditions Editorial policy Comments policy Syndication Privacy policy Cookies policy Links policy Accessibility Sitemap Other NHS sites Summary Care Records NHS Scotland NHS Northern Ireland NHS Wales NHS